        <productionVolumeComment xml:lang="en">Estimated value. Global production of gypsum in 2014 was of 176 600 000 tonnes (BGS 2016). The waste generation is estimated to be 15% (taken from the estimated value for gypsum (WRAP, n.d)). This results in 26 million tons of waste gypsum per annum. From previous version of ecoinvent, 70% of waste goes to inert material landfill, and 30% goes directly to sanitary landfill.
Given the assumptions made to derive this values, the amount of waste generated was cross-checked using GDP scaling (using the nominal GDP of 2005 (source: United Nations, http://data.un.org/Glossary.aspx?q=GDP+%28current+US%24%29, accessed 20130726 and 20130312)). Swiss production volume for waste gypsum is of 300 thousand tons and the GDP is of 0.0084 compared to the GLO one. This would result in 35 million tonnes of waste gypsum globally. 
References:
BGS (2016) World Mineral Production 2010-2014. 
WRAP (n.d.) International practice in plasterboard recycling: Canada. Retrieved from: http://www.wrap.org.uk/sites/files/wrap/Case%20study%20-%20Plasterboard%20recycling%20in%20Canada.pdf, accessed 3 May 2016</productionVolumeComment>
